The Lowveld Pie, Chips and Gravy Train met for the third time this year at Phat Boys in White River on Saturday March 26. Started by Thea Rix, Marius Bakkes and Dave Walters in 2019, the group is still going strong, with between 20 and 30 members usually meeting on the 21st of every month. ALSO READ: Young model may represent SA in South America Rix said last weekend’s meeting found excellent service and pies at Phat Boys Beer House. Rix has attended every single meeting since the start except one, due to her being in hospital. Attendees also shared photos of their food and their experience on the Lowveld Pie, Chips, and Gravy Train’s Facebook page. Visit the page to find out the date and venue of the fourth gathering. Do you have more information about the story? Please send us an email to editorial@lowvelder.co.za. For free breaking and community news, visit Lowvelder’s website: Lowvelder For more news and interesting articles, like Lowvelder on Facebook, follow us on Twitter or Instagram